##DESCRIPTION
## simple evaluation of a split domain function at a number
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##KEYWORDS('function', 'evaluation')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,12,1);
$b = random(1,12,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
For \( \displaystyle x<\frac{1}{$a} \), the function \( f(x)=|$a x-1|+$b \) is equivalent to the function \( g(x)=mx+b
\) for:
$BR
\( m= \)\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = -$a;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and$BR
\( b= \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =  1+$b;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Now for fun, try graphing \( f(x)\dots \)$BR
EOT

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
